Same Binary Tree (LeetCode 100)
Problem

Given two binary trees p and q, return true if both trees are exactly the same.

They are the same if:

✅ Structure is the same.
✅ Node values are the same.
Simple Idea

We compare both trees node by node using DFS (Recursion).

At every node, check:

Are both nodes NULL?
Is one NULL and the other not?
Are their values equal?
Compare left subtrees.
Compare right subtrees.

If all checks pass, the trees are the same.


class Solution {
public:
    bool isSameTree(TreeNode* p, TreeNode* q) {

        if (p == NULL && q == NULL)
            return true;

        if (p == NULL || q == NULL)
            return false;

        if (p->val != q->val)
            return false;

        return isSameTree(p->left, q->left) &&
               isSameTree(p->right, q->right);
    }
};
Interview Explanation (5 Simple Points)
I use DFS (recursion) to compare both trees node by node.
If both nodes are NULL, they are the same, so I return true.
If one node is NULL or the values are different, I return false.
Otherwise, I recursively compare the left subtree and the right subtree.
If both left and right comparisons return true, the trees are identical.






